description:
The DC-graftcopolymer can be prepared by several methods. In these methods, several intermediate products are previously prepared:

    A=a hydrophilic polymeric group comprising a terminal functional group G1;
    B=a hydrophobic polymeric group comprising a terminal functional group G2;
    C=a macromonomer formed by a chemical reaction between a monomer having a reactive group G3 and a hydrophilic polymeric group A having a reactive group G1 wherein G1 and G3 form a covalent bound;
    D=a macromonomer formed by a chemical reaction between a monomer having a reactive group G4 and a hydrophobic polymeric group B having a reactive group G2 wherein G1 and G4 form a covalent bound.
